                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "We refer to [12\u201314,19,21] and [24] as well as to references therein for more general Green function analysis of second order subelliptic (and weighted degenerate) operators.",
            "startOffset": 72600,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 70748,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "This question is inspired by M. Kac's question: Is there any boundary value problem for the Laplacian which is explicitly solvable in the classical sense for any smooth domain?",
            "startOffset": 70572,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 71049,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "The boundary conditions appearing there are, however, nonlocal and the corresponding boundary value problem can be called Kac's boundary value problem.",
            "startOffset": 70898,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 70572,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "The main aim of this short note is to give an answer to the question: Is there a class of domains in which the Dirichlet boundary value problem (1.1) is explicitly solvable in the classical sense?",
            "startOffset": 70376,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 77415,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "We also present solutions in an explicit form of the Dirichlet problem for the sub-Laplacian with non-zero boundary datum on those domains.",
            "startOffset": 77276,
            "title": "Green functions and representations of solutions"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 72922,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0080": {
                    "endOffset": 72793,
                    "startOffset": 72790
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "We also refer to [8] for a general point of view on H-type groups from the perspective of general stratified/graded/homogeneous/nilpotent Lie groups.",
            "startOffset": 72773,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 76336,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0020",
            "sentence": "The following version of Green's second formula will be useful for our analysis.",
            "startOffset": 76256,
            "title": "Preliminaries"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 71272,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "It is interesting to note that the explicit solutions in these papers have been constructed for Kac's boundary value problem for the sub-Laplacian equally well also in the presence of characteristic points on the boundary.",
            "startOffset": 71050,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 77275,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "In this section we construct, by using the classical method of reflection, Green functions of Dirichlet boundary value problems for sub-Laplacians on l-wedge like and l-strip like unbounded domains of a prototype H-type group.",
            "startOffset": 77049,
            "title": "Green functions and representations of solutions"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 73221,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "In Section 3 we construct Green functions and give representation formulae for solutions.",
            "startOffset": 73132,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 86597,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0030",
                    "title": "Green functions and representations of solutions"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0050",
            "sentence": "Similar to proof of Theorem 3.2.",
            "startOffset": 86565,
            "title": "Green functions and representations of solutions in l-strip spaces"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 86600,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0030",
                    "title": "Green functions and representations of solutions"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0050",
            "sentence": "\u25a1",
            "startOffset": 86599,
            "title": "Green functions and representations of solutions in l-strip spaces"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 76477,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0020": {
                    "endOffset": 76392,
                    "startOffset": 76389
                },
                "br0240": {
                    "endOffset": 76448,
                    "startOffset": 76426
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0020",
            "sentence": "It goes back to the integration by parts formula in [2] but the following form (given in [23, Proposition 3.10]) will be useful for us here.",
            "startOffset": 76337,
            "title": "Preliminaries"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 70897,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0210": {
                    "endOffset": 70813,
                    "startOffset": 70809
                },
                "br0240": {
                    "endOffset": 70850,
                    "startOffset": 70846
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "An answer to M. Kac's question was given in our recent paper [20] for the Heisenberg group and in [23] for general homogeneous stratified Lie groups.",
            "startOffset": 70748,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 73027,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0230": {
                    "endOffset": 73026,
                    "startOffset": 73022
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "For functional inequalities on stratified Lie groups and further literature review we can refer to [22].",
            "startOffset": 72923,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 77475,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "Of course, the results are well known in the abelian cases.",
            "startOffset": 77416,
            "title": "Green functions and representations of solutions"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 76514,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0020",
            "sentence": "Green's second formula",
            "startOffset": 76492,
            "title": "Preliminaries"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 73131,
            "parents": [],
